Input Attributes:
The input disabled attribute specifies that an input field should be disabled. A disabled input field is unusable and un-clickable.
The input size attribute specifies the visible width, in characters, of an input field. The default value for size is 20.
The input maxlength attribute specifies the maximum number of characters allowed in an input field.
The input min and max attributes specify the minimum and maximum values for an input field.
The min and max attributes work with the following input types: number, range, date, datetime-local, month, time and week.
The input placeholder attribute specifies a short hint that describes the expected value of an input field (a sample value or a short description of the expected format).
The input required attribute specifies that an input field must be filled out before submitting the form.

MODULE 2 - CSS OVERVIEW

In this example all <p> elements will be center-aligned, with a red text color:
p {
  color: red;
  text-align: center;
}

The id selector (#) character, followed by the id of the element.
To select elements class, (.) character, followed by the class name.

In this example only <p> elements with class="center" will be red and center-aligned: 
p.center {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}

color 
text-align
background-color = property specifies the background color of an element.
opacity = specifies the opacity/transparency of an element. It can take a value from 0.0 - 1.0.
background-image = url("paper.gif");
background-repeat: repeat-x;
background-repeat: no-repeat = Showing the background image only once
background-position: right top;
background-attachment: fixed/scroll
border-style = dotted/dashed/solid/double/none/hidden
border-width = 5px/medium/thick/2px/ 5px 20px  /* 5px top and bottom, 20px on the sides */









